/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~       \/      \/         \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

To  add  an  item  to the Playlist simply click on the @{FG SHINE}'Add Item'@{FG TEXT} gadget.  A
file  requester will then be displayed.  Choose the file you wish to add and
it will be placed at the end of the current Playlist.
@ENDNODE
@NODE DELETE "Deleting an item from the Playlist"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /       @{fg text}Script File Generator@{fg shine}
 //       \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~       \/      \/         \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

Clicking  on  the  @{FG SHINE}'Delete  Item'@{FG TEXT}  gadget  will  remove the last item in the
playlist.
@ENDNODE
@NODE CLEAR "Clearing the Playlist"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /       @{fg text}Script File Generator@{fg shine}
 //       \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~       \/      \/         \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}
By clicking on the @{FG SHINE}'Clear List'@{FG TEXT} icon, all the items in the Playlist will be
removed.
@ENDNODE
@NODE TOOLTYPES "SFMV Script Generator TOOLTYPES"
@{fg shine}  _____________________________   ____      @{FG FILL}@{"Main SFMV Guide" LINK SFMV:Guides/SFMV.Guide/MAIN}@{FG SHINE}
 /'  _____/\_   _____/'    \`  \ /'  /
 \_____ ~\  |'   __)/  \ /  \   X   /       @{fg text}Script File Generator@{fg shine}
 //       \ |     \/    Y    \     /
/_______  / \___  /\____|__  /\___/
~       \/      \/         \/@{fg text}
@{u}                                                                           @{uu}

The following TOOLTYPES can be used to alter the way that the program works.

@{FG SHINE}@{U}TOOLTYPE		Description@{UU}@{FG TEXT}

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}MAXITEMS@{FG TEXT}		Maximum  number  of  items that can be placed in the
			playlist.  Defaults to 64 items.  Setting this value
			too high could cause out of memory errors.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}WARNINGS@{FG TEXT}		This  can be set to TRUE, FALSE, ON or OFF.  Warning
			requesters  occur  when the program can not identify
			the files that it reads.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}SCRIPTPATH@{FG TEXT}		This  is  the  default  path  for loading and saving
			script files.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}DATAPATH@{FG TEXT}		This is the default path for the SFMV, IFF and music
			files.


An example tooltype entry....

@{FG FILL}MAXITEMS = 50
WARNINGS = FALSE
SCRIPTPATH = DH1:SFMV/SCRIPTS
(DATAPATH= RAM:)@{FG TEXT}

This  sets  the  maximum  number  of  items in a playlist to 50 files.  File
identification  warnings  are  turned  off  and  the  default script path is
"DH1:SFMV/SCRIPTS".   The data path has been disabled, therefore the current
directory will be use as the default data path.
@ENDNODE
